data.description: NEW PRICE! TAKE A SECOND LOOK!  (Renovated house across the street sold for M$1.14 in August 2023. )  HOUSE IS FRESHLY PAINTED, DEEP-CLEANED  AND READY  FOR MOVE-IN while updating over time to suit your personal style.  ESTATE SALE, APPROVED BY THIRD PARTY FOR IMMEDIATE SALE. Sold AS-IS, but extremely Move-in Ready and livable.  This Home was built in 1926, well-maintained and owned by the same family for decades and first time on market.  You'll love this Semi-Detached 3 BDRM 2.5 BA Colonial End Rowhouse with High Ceilings, original Hardwood Floors throughout, Original Woodwork and Glass Doorknobs. Large Main Bedroom has its own Bath/Shower and Big Windows.  Full Bath on Upper Level and Half Bath in Basement.  Main Level has Spacious open Livingroom with Fireplace, High Ceilings, Large Windows and opens into Separate Dining Room with original Chandelier. Updated Eat-in Kitchen has Granite Countertops, Stainless Appliances, Gas Stove  and lots of Cabinets.  There are multiple Window A/Cs and Ceiling Fans throughout.  All Windows have Blinds. Updated plumbing and Laundry area with full-sized W/D in Basement Laundry area. Spacious Basement has a bar area with seating.  Rear Door to backyard. There's a Detached One-Car GARAGE and long, Shared-Driveway for extra Parking, along with easy parking in front.   Fenced landscaped Backyard. Lots of features to be admired.  Termite inspection and Treatment completed. Annual seasonal precision Tune-Up of HVAC System recently completed. Current ITEMS OF FURNITURE REMAINING IN HOUSE ARE SUBJECT TO NEGOTIATION.  Home and  existing Appliances are being sold in their STRICTLY AS-IS condition.   Cash or Mortgage Pre-Approval from a reputable lender;  Acknowledged receipt of of EMD/and or Proof of Funds with Cash Offers required.   Seller Reserves the Right to Accept or Reject Any Offer. MOVE-IN FOR THE HOLIDAYS!
